   Schedule Updates

                                _____________
                               E-Mail Address
                                  Subscribe

   [dot.jpg]

   Tuesday, February 5, 2002

   10:00 a.m., in 2322 Rayburn House Office Building
   The Subcommittee on Oversight and Investigations has scheduled a
   hearing for Tuesday, February 5, 2002, at 10:00 a.m., in 2322 Rayburn
   House Office Building. This will be the first day of the hearing on the
   Financial Collapse of Enron Corp. This day will focus on the findings
   of Enrons special investigative committee with respect to certain
   transactions between Enron and certain of its current and former
   officers and employees. Mr. William C. Powers, Jr., chairman of Enrons
   special investigative committee, will be the only witness.

   Wednesday, February 6, 2002

   12:30 p.m. in 345 Cannon House Office Building
   The Committee on Energy and Commerce hearing scheduled for Tuesday,
   January 29, 2002, and Wednesday, January 30, 2002, on developments
   relating to Enron Corp., including its relationship with Andersen LLP,
   has been rescheduled to Wednesday, February 6, 2002, at 12:30 p.m. in
   345 Cannon House Office Building.  Witnesses will be by invitation
   only.

   Thursday, February 7, 2002

   9:30 a.m., in 2322 Rayburn House Office Building
   The Subcommittee on Oversight and Investigations has scheduled a
   hearing for Thursday, February 7, 2002, at 9:30 a.m., in 2322 Rayburn
   House Office Building. This will be the second day of the hearing on
   the Financial Collapse of Enron Corp. This day will continue to focus
   on certain transactions between Enron and certain of its current and
   former officers and employees. Witnesses will be by invitation only.


   Note on Audio Broadcasting:

   The audio of all Committee hearings are broadcast via the Internet.
   The Committee's webcasting capacity is limited, so please visit
   http://www.house.gov/commerce 15 minutes prior to the beginning of the
   event. The free Real Player is also required. (http://www.real.com)
   Please note that Committee markups are not currently broadcast.
   Accessible Facilities:

   [handsym.gif] The Committee endeavors to make its facilities accessible
   to persons with disabilities. If you are in need of special
   accommodations, or have any questions regarding special accommodations
   generally, please contact the Committee in advance of the scheduled
   event (4 business days notice is requested) at (202) 225-2927; TTY#
   (202) 225-1904; or 2125 Rayburn House Office Building.

